#  configurations without code changes:
#
#  1. Multiple Authentication Methods
#
#  - Windows Authentication: DB_TRUSTED_CONNECTION=true (current
#  setup)
#  - SQL Server Authentication: DB_TRUSTED_CONNECTION=false with
#  username/password
#
#  2. Dynamic Connection Configuration
#
#  The application supports changing via .env file:
#  # For Production SQL Server with SQL Authentication:
#  DB_SERVER=prod-sql-server.company.com
#  DB_PORT=1433
#  DB_DATABASE=ProductionDB
#  DB_USERNAME=app_user
#  DB_PASSWORD=secure_password
#  DB_TRUSTED_CONNECTION=false
#  DB_ENCRYPT=true  # For production security
#
#  3. Multiple Database Connections
#
#  The Connection Manager already handles multiple databases:
#  - 6 existing connections configured in user_connections table
#  - Web UI for adding new connections at
#  http://127.0.0.1:5000/connections
#  - Real-time connection testing and validation
#  - Per-job connection selection (each job can use different
#  database)
#
#  4. Production-Ready Features
#
#  - Encryption support: DB_ENCRYPT=true/false
#  - Certificate trust options: DB_TRUST_SERVER_CERTIFICATE=true/false    
#  - Connection timeouts: Configurable via DB_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT
#  - Connection pooling: Built-in SQLAlchemy pooling
#  - Connection validation: Tests connections before job execution        
#
#  5. Easy Environment Changes
#
#  Just update .env and restart - no code changes needed:
#  # Development
#  DB_SERVER=localhost\SQLEXPRESS
#  DB_TRUSTED_CONNECTION=true
#
#  # Production  
#  DB_SERVER=prod-server.domain.com
#  DB_TRUSTED_CONNECTION=false
